text: Kjell Engebretsen (born 29 April 1941 in Oslo) is a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Akershus in 1993, and was re-elected on two occasions. Engebretsen was a member of Frogn municipality council in the periods 1983-1987 and 1991-1993\. During these periods he was also a member of Akershus county council. ==References== * Category:1941 births Category:Living people Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:21st-century Norwegian politicians Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
